This paper proposes an efficient framework for convolutional neural networks (CNN) to be used on mobile devices, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on reducing computation complexity, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses quantization of filter kernels and weighting matrices, which suggests that it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for mobile devices to accurately classify images, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
